<subSubSection id="2EAF6C865AAB831204B586E599B2CD1F" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="35D3FAE38C41F368E91C511BA9AFE5AB" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3A7A1252F92A009FF45FE1F5145E79B7" pageNumber="42">Distinguished from all other cynolebiatins by two unambiguous synapomorphies (Costa, 2006a): a long (vs. short) hyomandibula and a narrowed (vs. wide) proximal tip of the fourth ceratobranchial.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
