<normalizedToken id="BED650ECCF2634D9C225E1ACEB7BAAEF" originalValue="rÃ­o">rio</normalizedToken>
Paraguay basin (Figs. 1 and 4).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8415D1772976B944BE14FACE32377BCE" type="key">
<paragraph id="A7591E60EA6D4FCF800437747695F385" pageNumber="42">
Key to species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="229D02127D8109E37D94E5B7BB74669B" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Spectrolebias">Spectrolebias</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A1BB547E3756F81605CEF40952D47E43" pageNumber="42">1a. Dorsal fin rounded in males; dark suborbital and postorbital bars........................................................2</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BA83928A7D6D7E3D8DD0FFCB89BD0C3C" pageNumber="42">1b. Dorsal fin pointed in males; no bars on head........................................................................................3</paragraph>
<paragraph id="87395F08838D1657BA6F6BF26C6AD400" pageNumber="42">
2a(1a). Dorsal-fin rays 23-25 in males, 13-15 in females; flank greenish blue with dark red crimson scale margins in males................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="288F7A4873E1DF4A4BC0ACBE17954651" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E7DE1DBB-323D-4D69-8018-A1305DB00333" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Simpsonichthys reticulatus Costa &amp; Nielsen 2003:120" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="reticulatus">S. reticulatus</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F40DFD3916C794724FA535894C0D6C0D" pageNumber="42">
2b(1a). Dorsal-fin rays 21-23 in males, 16-19 in females; flank dark brown to black with light blue dots in males.......................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="53F6E5274F55CB094040B5AD396A7D62" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="costai">S. costai</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9D953D000191925EF3659171B505E24D" pageNumber="42">3a(1b). Anal-fin rays 23-25 in males; flanks light orange to translucent, unpaired fins pale red in males........................................4</paragraph>
<paragraph id="630A7138375DD3DE7FF9C41D521E9974" pageNumber="42">
3b(1b). Anal-fin rays 26-28 in males; flanks and unpaired fins dark bluish gray in males............................... 
<taxonomicName id="05829B3999160FFE7E48980F1033424F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chacoensis">S. chacoensis</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8CE5D1718EEE54E6484EE1F4949347A7" pageNumber="42">
4a(3a). Frontal squamation E-patterned; anal fin pointed and with long filaments in males; no black spot on anal fin in males.............................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="09FDC8E79FEC8C001EF3AC08241BE76B" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E7FB220C-5585-4FCE-BBF6-7B6F233844EA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Simpsonichthys filamentosus Costa, Barrera &amp; Sarmiento 1997:84" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="filamentosus">S. filamentosus</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="080B5570E3AE7B5459407E73D23214D1" pageNumber="42">
4b(3a). Frontal squamation F-patterned; anal fin rounded and without filaments in males; black and blue spot on posterior portion of distal edge of anal fin in males................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="D2D4956F9BD917B40281B1B899F071D9" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:09CC5243-7D7E-455D-8629-7067392C8C0D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Spectrolebias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Spectrolebias semiocellatus Costa &amp; Nielsen 1997:259" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="semiocellatus">S. semiocellatus</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
